# Dependency Injection (DI) 💉

## 📖 What is Dependency Injection (DI)?

**Dependency Injection (DI)** is a design pattern in which an object receives its dependencies from an external source instead of creating them itself.

In Spring Framework, the **Spring IoC Container** creates and injects the required objects (Beans).

In simple words:

> **Don't create objects manually. Let Spring create and manage them for you.**

---

# 🎯 Why Dependency Injection?

Without DI:

❌ Tight Coupling

❌ Difficult Testing

❌ Hard to Maintain

❌ Difficult to Replace Components

With DI:

✅ Loose Coupling

✅ Easy Testing

✅ Better Code Reusability

✅ Easy Maintenance

---

