# 🏗 Without Dependency Injection

```java id="jlwm2"
class Engine {

    void start() {
        System.out.println("Engine Started");
    }

}

class Car {

    private Engine engine =
            new Engine();

    void drive() {
        engine.start();
        System.out.println("Car Running");
    }

}
```

Problem:

* Tight Coupling
* Difficult to modify
* Difficult to test

---

# 🏗 With Dependency Injection

```java id="jlwm3"
class Engine {

    void start() {
        System.out.println("Engine Started");
    }

}

class Car {

    private Engine engine;

    Car(Engine engine) {
        this.engine = engine;
    }

}
```

Spring provides the Engine object.

